&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overuse of animations and transitions&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;key-points&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Key Points&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using a consistent color scheme across all slides&lt;/strong&gt; helps in maintaining a professional and cohesive look throughout the presentation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Choosing visually attractive fonts that are also easy to read&lt;/strong&gt; ensures that the text is both engaging and legible, which enhances the audience&amp;#39;s understanding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using high-quality images and graphics&lt;/strong&gt; can make the presentation more visually appealing and can help in better illustrating the points being discussed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overuse of animations and transitions&lt;/strong&gt; can be distracting and may detract from the main content of the presentation. Hence, it is not suggested.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;additional-info&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Additional Information&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Avoid cluttering slides with too much information. Keep the slides simple and focused on the key points.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make sure that the text contrast with the background to ensure readability.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use bullet points to break down information into digestible parts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Practice good alignment and spacing to make the presentation visually balanced.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Rehearse the presentation to ensure smooth delivery and timing of animations or transitions used.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
