&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2) (i) False, (ii) True&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;key-points&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Key Point Icon&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Key Points&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Statement (i): &lt;strong&gt;False&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Operating systems and device drivers are indeed examples of system software. They play crucial roles in managing and controlling the computer hardware and providing a platform for application software to run.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Statement (ii): &lt;strong&gt;True&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The main purpose of system software is to manage and control computer hardware. This includes tasks such as managing memory, processing tasks, and handling input and output operations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;additional-info&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Additional Information Icon&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Additional Information&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;System software acts as an intermediary between the hardware and the user applications, ensuring that the hardware is used efficiently.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Examples of system software include operating systems (e.g., Windows, macOS, Linux), device drivers, utility programs, and firmware.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Without system software, it would be nearly impossible to operate a computer, as users would have to manage hardware resources directly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
